<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BLAST DAMAGES DOOR OF ATTORNEY'S HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An explosion damaged the front door of an attorney's house in Van Nuys, Los 
Angeles police reported Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The blast occurred near midnight Wednesday at the home of Robert Klein in the 
15900 block of Haynes Street, police said. No one was hurt. 
</P>
<P>
An unknown explosive material was used, and the force of the blast heavily 
damaged the door and shattered a window in the door, Detective Robert Muldrew 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The case is being investigated by the bomb squad and the department's Criminal 
Conspiracy Unit. Police said that there were no suspects and the explosion may 
have been a prank. 
</P>
