MORNING REPORT: RADIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Liz Kiley, assistant program director and music director at KOST-FM, will 
become program director at KFAC-FM on Aug. 14, further fueling the widespread 
speculation that KFAC will change from its longtime classical format to a 
contemporary hits or rock station. Kiley also has been the on-air host for 
KOST's "Love Songs on the Coast." ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
