<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New York's Museum of Modern Art Thursday placed on view Vincent Van Gogh's 
"Portrait of Joseph Roulin," which it recently acquired from a private Swiss 
collection. The painting, the fourth of a series of portraits of the postmaster 
of Arles, France, was completed early in 1889, a year before Van Gogh's death, 
and is considered one of the expressionist's finest works from the French 
countryside. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
