<P>
TEXAS ENACTS FLAG LAW TO COUNTER COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Texas Gov. Bill Clements signed a bill establishing a new state flag 
desecration law to replace the one thrown out by the Supreme Court. The 
measure, similar to one pending in Congress, makes it a crime to desecrate the 
American flag and does not include language that the Supreme Court found 
objectionable when it ruled in June that flag burning was a protected form of 
free speech. The new Texas law also makes it a crime to desecrate the state 
flag. President Bush has argued that the court's ruling cannot be overturned 
with a simple bill, either at the state or federal level, contending that a 
constitutional amendment is needed to give the states and the Congress the 
power to draft bills against flag desecration. The Texas Legislature has also 
passed a resolution urging Congress to approve the constitutional change. 
</P>
