<HEADLINE>
<P>
A STOP FOR BREAKFAST COOKS MAN'S GOOSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOBILE, Ala. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An aroma of bacon and eggs led to the arrest of the cook, who was at the stove 
but not in his own house. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. Mike Barton said Mike Richardson, 25, was being sought by Florida and 
Alabama state police on a stolen car charge when he apparently left Interstate 
10 for breakfast Wednesday in Mobile. 
</P>
<P>
Residents of the house called police when they awoke at 1:45 a.m., smelling 
breakfast. 
</P>
<P>
Richardson was treated for a hand injury he suffered when officers interrupted 
his breakfast. He was charged with burglary and assault. 
</P>
