<TEXT>
<P>
Freddie Spencer, former world motorcycle champion in the 250cc and 500cc 
classes, was dismissed by Marlboro Yamaha just three days before the British 
Grand Prix in Donington, England. 
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old American, who in 1985 became the first rider to win the 250 and 
500 titles in the same season, was also the youngest winner of the 500cc 
championship. 
</P>
