</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
COACHES UNANIMOUS -- FRESNO ST. WILL REPEAT IN BIG WEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fresno State, which won the Big West football title last season by going 
undefeated against conference teams, was chosen unanimously to repeat as 
champion in a poll of coaches Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Fresno State went 10-2 overall last season, losing only to Colorado and Oregon 
State. The Bulldogs defeated Western Michigan in the postseason California 
Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
San Jose State, which went undefeated in the conference while winning titles in 
1986 and 1987 but fell to 4-3 in conference games and 4-8 overall last year, 
was predicted to finish second. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton, 5-6 and 5-2 in 1988, was rated fourth, and Cal State Long 
Beach, 3-9 and 3-4, sixth. ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
