<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY STARS PLAY FOR CLASSIC CROWN SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN DROOZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The South Bay Stars will face a team from Obregon Park at 11:45 a.m. Saturday 
for the championship of the youth Summer Baseball Classic at Bodger Park in 
Hawthorne. 
</P>
<P>
The Stars are 4-0 in the tourney and are coming off a 3-0 victory Wednesday 
over Jesse Owens Park. Jo Jo Triana has won all four games and will be the 
starting pitcher Saturday. He has pitched 15 scoreless innings with 24 
strikeouts. 
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's game was decided by a two-run double in the third inning by first 
baseman Kevin McCarthy. 
</P>
<P>
The Stars have outscored opponents, 33-6. Triana has five hits and six RBIs. 
Brandon Veit has six hits and Joshua Canales has scored nine runs, with leadoff 
man Johnny Walter scoring seven. 
</P>
<P>
In earlier games, the Stars defeated Campanella Park, 14-0, in the first round, 
Ford Park (Bell Gardens), 5-2, in the second round and the Lynwood All-Stars, 
11-4, in the third round. ALAN DROOZ 
</P>
