ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: ORANGE; 
</P>
<P>
HEART ATTACK ON FREEWAY KILLS 79-YEAR-OLD DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 79-year-old Hemet man died of an apparent heart attack he suffered Thursday 
while driving with his wife on the Costa Mesa Freeway in Orange, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Willard F. Burch lost control of his car while northbound on the freeway, north 
of Chapman Avenue. His car careened across the car-pool lane, hitting the 
center divider. Burch's vehicle then was hit from behind by a car driven by a 
54-year-old Corona man traveling in the car-pool lane, a California Highway 
Patrol spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Burch died shortly after the 2:45 p.m. accident. 
</P>
