<TEXT>
<P>
South Coast Plaza, which opened in 1967, ranks No. 1 in the state in gross 
annual sales for planned retail centers. The shopping complex is anchored by 
three department stores and three major specialty stores, and offers more than 
200 specialty shops such as Tiffany &amp; Co., Cartier, Polo/Ralph Lauren and 
Jaeger. New stores scheduled to open in 1989-90 include Burberrys of London, 
Lenox, Jose Eber, Georg Jensen and Barneys New York. 
