<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE; 
</P>
<P>
MINISTER WHO ALLEGED ATTACKS QUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A lesbian minister who said she was attacked by two homophobic "skinheads" 
abruptly resigned today amid speculation that she fabricated that and another 
report. 
</P>
<P>
Lynn Griffis, 27, assistant pastor at the Metropolitan Community Church, 
claimed that on July 28 she was dragged into a car by two skinheads who beat 
her and threatened to kill her because she was a lesbian who helped AIDS 
victims. 
</P>
<P>
Two weeks before, Griffis reported being attacked in her home for the same 
reasons by an intruder with a shovel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
