<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
MAN MISSING OFF WILL ROGERS BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 20-year-old man on vacation from the Sacramento area disappeared during a 
predawn swim in the surf along Will Rogers State Beach today, prompting a 
search by lifeguards and a Coast Guard helicopter, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The names of the missing man and his friend, also 20 and from the Sacramento 
area, were not immediately released. The two drove from their motel in Los 
Angeles to Will Rogers State Beach in Pacific Palisades early today and decided 
to go swimming about 4:45 a.m., county Lifeguard Lt. Randy DeGregori said. The 
man had been drinking heavily, his friend said. 
</P>
