<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
5 RESCUED FROM CAPSIZED SAILBOAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A freighter rescued the five crew members of a sailboat that capsized in the 
Pacific en route to California from Hawaii on Thursday night after the classic 
long-distance Transpac race. 
</P>
<P>
The San Francisco-based Pandemonium overturned about 300 miles west of San 
Francisco after its keel broke off, Coast Guard Chief Petty Officer Egbert 
Vallecillo said. 
</P>
<P>
A jetliner picked up the racing sailboat's emergency beacon just before 5 p.m. 
Thursday. A Coast Guard plane spotted the four men and one woman in two 
lifeboats near the sailboat and asked the crew of a nearby freighter to pick 
them up. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
